## ğŸ¯ Suggested File Naming Convention

### Option A: By Product ID
```
products/
  product-1.jpg    (Aged Cheddar)
  product-2.jpg    (Greek Feta)
  product-3.jpg    (Mozzarella)
  product-11.jpg   (Beef Steak)
  product-21.jpg   (Prosciutto)
  product-31.jpg   (Sourdough)
  product-41.jpg   (Milk)
  ...
```

### Option B: By Product Name (Slug)
```
products/
  aged-cheddar.jpg
  greek-feta.jpg
  mozzarella-buffalo.jpg
  prime-beef-steak.jpg
  italian-prosciutto.jpg
  artisan-sourdough.jpg
  organic-milk.jpg
  ...
```

### Category Images
```
categories/
  cheese.jpg
  fresh-meat.jpg
  deli.jpg
  bread.jpg
  dairy.jpg
  drinks.jpg
  grocery-items.jpg
  christmas.jpg
  halloween.jpg
```

### Retailer Logos
```
retailers/
  groceryco.jpg
  freshmart.jpg
  meatmarket.jpg
  delicorner.jpg
  bakeryplus.jpg
  dairydirect.jpg
  supersave.jpg
```

---

## ğŸ”— How to Use Your Images

### Step 1: Upload to GitHub
1. Create a public GitHub repository (e.g., `wave-grocery-assets`)
2. Organize images using one of the naming conventions above
3. Push your images to the repository

### Step 2: Get Raw URLs
GitHub raw URLs follow this pattern:
```
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/YOUR_USERNAME/REPO_NAME/main/path/to/image.jpg
```

Example:
```
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/john-doe/wave-grocery-assets/main/products/product-1.jpg
```

### Step 3: Update the Code
Let me know when your images are uploaded and I'll update:
- `/components/ProductCatalogueView.tsx` - Product images
- `/components/CategoriesView.tsx` - Category images
- `/components/CartView.tsx` - Retailer logos

---

## ğŸ“ Image Dimensions & Specifications

### Product Images (Catalogue & Cart)
- **Aspect Ratio**: 1:1 (Square)
- **Recommended Size**: 400Ã—400px or 800Ã—800px
- **Minimum Size**: 300Ã—300px
- **Maximum Size**: 1200Ã—1200px
- **Format**: JPG or PNG
- **Usage**: 
  - Product catalogue grid (displayed in square tiles)
  - Cart items (72Ã—72px thumbnails)
  - Product detail views

### Category Images

#### Themed Categories (Christmas, Halloween, etc.)
- **Aspect Ratio**: Flexible (displayed at 168px min-height)
- **Recommended Size**: 400Ã—400px or 600Ã—600px
- **Format**: JPG or PNG
- **Display**: Full card coverage with gradient overlay
- **Usage**: Homepage category cards (2-column grid)

#### Product Categories (Cheese, Meat, Dairy, etc.)
- **Aspect Ratio**: Flexible, portrait or square works best
- **Recommended Size**: 400Ã—500px or 500Ã—600px
- **Maximum Height**: 140px (when displayed)
- **Format**: PNG with transparent background preferred, or JPG
- **Display**: Contained within card with padding
- **Usage**: Categories view grid (2-column layout, 208px min-height cards)

### Retailer Logos
- **Aspect Ratio**: 1:1 (Square) preferred
- **Recommended Size**: 200Ã—200px or 400Ã—400px
- **Minimum Size**: 100Ã—100px
- **Format**: PNG with transparent background preferred
- **Usage**:
  - Product tile badges (16Ã—16px display)
  - Cart retailer headers (larger display)
  - Checkout screens

### Banner/Carousel Images (Homepage)
- **Aspect Ratio**: ~16:9 or 2:1 (landscape)
- **Recommended Size**: 750Ã—400px or 1125Ã—600px
- **Width**: Match container width (343px on mobile)
- **Format**: JPG or PNG
- **Usage**: Homepage carousel/banner area

---

## ğŸ“ Image Quality Guidelines

- **Format**: 
  - Use PNG for logos and images requiring transparency
  - Use JPG for photographs and product images
- **Compression**: Optimize images to keep file sizes under 200KB per image
- **Quality**: 80-90% quality for JPG is ideal
- **Consistency**: 
  - Use similar lighting/style across product images
  - Maintain consistent background (white or transparent recommended)
  - Keep composition centered and consistent
- **Color Profile**: sRGB recommended for web display

